  "title": "Infant Educarer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>We are looking for candidates to join us as:</p><ol><li>Infant Teacher with Higher Certificate in Infant Care/Advanced Certificate in Early Years.</li><li>Assistant Teacher (CCP - HCIC/ACEY)</li></ol><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ol><li>To take charge of a group of infants in planning and carrying out the daily developmental and caregiving tasks.</li><li>Attend to the health, hygiene and safety needs of the infants.</li><li>Build trusting and respectful partnerships with parents and families.</li><li>Create a safe environment and provide the best possible care to infants under their charge.</li><li>Assist in implementing a developmentally and culturally appropriate curriculum to provide a quality learning environment.</li><li>Create a secure environment for young children through enhancing respectful, responsive and reciprocal relationships with them.</li><li>Actively engages in and contributes to Centre initiatives.</li><li>Shall achieve at least 25 hours of CPD, including courses and other CPD activities, in the calendar year.</li></ol><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Good written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Classroom and project management skills</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Able to manage stress</li><li>Passion for teaching children</li></ul><p>Interested candidate may Whatsapp: 92315917 (Ms Jessica)</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
